blockStates.name: Molecular Structures
blockStates.userText:
In chemistry, molecular visualization 
is the discipline of studying molecules 
and their properties through graphical 
representation, usually in 3D computer
graphics.

The Molecular Viewer Block provides
3D visualization that displays molecular 
structures in an interactive way. You
can import the molecular data through
the Data Block by connecting the output
of the Data Block to the initialization port
(Port I) of the Molecular Viewer Block.
The Data Block supports PDB and 
XYZ formats.

The X, Y, and Z ports of a Molecular
Viewer Block are reserved to receive 
updates of the atomic coordinates. 
It can be used to create molecular 
animations through molecular simulation.

This page uses four different structures
formed by carbon atoms as examples.
Although they are all made of carbon,
their chemical and physical properties
are quite different.
